message.content:
Analysis of the Main Target Image
--------------------------------
• Total Blocks and Layers  
  – There are 8 total blocks.  
  – They form roughly 4 vertical “levels”:  
    1) Bottom “legs” (two blue cubes, one on each side, plus the lower half of the red column in the center).  
    2) A yellow horizontal bridging block spanning between the two blue cubes, plus the upper half of the red column.  
    3) One green rectangular block on top of the red column.  
    4) Two orange triangular wedges forming the “roof.”  

• Spatial Arrangement  
  – Bottom Layer: One blue cube on the left, one blue cube on the right, with a red cube in the center rear.  
  – Second Layer: Another red cube stacked atop the first red cube, and a single yellow rectangular block bridging across the two blue cubes.  
  – Third Layer: A green rectangular block sits on top of the two stacked red cubes.  
  – Fourth Layer (Roof): Two orange triangular wedges lean inward to create a pitched roof.  

Selection of Dictionary Blocks
------------------------------
Matching each piece exactly (shape, color, and orientation, without rotating them differently than shown in the dictionary) yields:

1) Blue cube (left leg) → Block #1  
2) Blue cube (right leg) → Block #3  
3) Red cube (center bottom) → Block #2  
4) Red cube (center top) → Block #2 (reused)  
5) Yellow horizontal block (bridge) → Block #8  
6) Green horizontal block (top band) → Block #4  
7) Orange triangular wedge (roof left) → Block #13  
8) Orange triangular wedge (roof right) → Block #14  

Assembly Instructions
---------------------
{
  Step1: Move block with index 1    // Place the left blue cube  
  Step2: Move block with index 3    // Place the right blue cube  
  Step3: Move block with index 2    // Place the first red cube in the center  
  Step4: Move block with index 2    // Stack the second red cube on the first  
  Step5: Move block with index 8    // Bridge the two blue cubes with the yellow block  
  Step6: Move block with index 4    // Place the green rectangular block atop the red cubes  
  Step7: Move block with index 13   // Position the left orange roof wedge  
  Step8: Move block with index 14   // Position the right orange roof wedge  
}
